Alternated ridge lfmm vs analytic ridge lfmm

kevin caye

19 janvier 2017

library(tidyverse)
library(Article3Package)

On Sample from AT data set

G.file <- "~/Projects/Data2016_2017/AthalianaGegMapLines/call_method_75/call_method_75_TAIR9.G.rds"
K <- 3
s <- FromTrueSampler(G.file = G.file,
                     n = 200,
                     L = 1000,
                     K = K,
                     prop.outlier = 0.1,
                     rho = 0.9,
                     cs = c(0.9,0,0),
                     round = FALSE) 
  set.seed(0)
  AlternatedVsAnalyticRidge(s = s,
                            method.K = K,
                            exp.rep = 1,
                            lambda = 10)
Hypothesis testing comparison 
Estimation comparison

On Gaussian dataset

K <- 3
s <- NormalSampler(100, 1000, 
                   K,
                   prop.outlier = 0.2,
                   c = 0.0)
  
  set.seed(0)
  AlternatedVsAnalyticRidge(s = s,
                            method.K = K,
                            exp.rep = 1,
                            lambda = 1e-3)
